investigation.title: Nrf2 alleviates spaceflight-induced immunosuppression and thrombotic microangiopathy in mice
investigation.description: Spaceflight-related stresses impact health via various body systems, including the haematopoietic and immune systems, with effects ranging from moderate alterations of homoeostasis to serious illness. Oxidative stress appears to be involved in these changes, and the transcription factor Nrf2, which regulates expression of a set of cytoprotective and antioxidative stress response genes, has been implicated in the response to spaceflight-induced stresses.

project.funding: This work was selected as a space rodent research study for JAXA’s feasibility experiments using ISS/Kibo announced in 2015, and also supported in part by MEXT/JSPS KAKENHI (19H03555 to R.S., 19H05649 to M.Y., and 18H04963 to T. Suzuki), BINDS/AMED (JP22ama121038 to M.Y.) and the Smart Aging Research Center, Tohoku University (M.Y.). This work was also supported in part by the grants JP19km0105001 and JP19km0105002.
